                                                                                                @NotNull
                                                                                                Channel.InputChannel<?>... channels)
        Returns a builder of channels distributing the input data among the specified channels. If the list of data is smaller than the specified number of channels, the remaining ones will be fed with the specified placeholder instance. While, if the list of data exceeds the number of channels, the invocation will be aborted.

      • groupBy

        @NotNull
 @StreamFlow(value=MAP,
            binding=ROUTINE)
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,List<DATA>> groupBy(int size)
        Returns a factory of invocations grouping the input data in collections of the specified size.

        Given a numeric sequence of inputs starting from 0, and a size of 3, the final output will be: 

             

         [(0, 1, 2), (3, 4, 5), ..., (N, N + 1)]
        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        size - the group size.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the size is not positive.

      • groupBy

        @NotNull
 @StreamFlow(value=MAP,
            binding=ROUTINE)
public static <DATA> InvocationFactory<DATA,List<DATA>> groupBy(int size,
                                                                                                                              @Nullable
                                                                                                                              DATA placeholder)
        Returns a factory of invocations grouping the input data in collections of the specified size.
        If the inputs complete and the last group length is less than the target size, the missing spaces will be filled with the specified placeholder instance.

        Given a numeric sequence of inputs starting from 0, and a size of 3, the final output will be: 

             

         [(0, 1, 2), (3, 4, 5), ..., (N, N + 1, PH)]
        Type Parameters:
        DATA - the data type.
        Parameters:
        size - the group size.
        placeholder - the placeholder object used to fill the missing data needed to reach the group size.
        Returns:
        the invocation factory.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the size is not positive.

      • join

        @NotNull
public static <OUT> ChannelsBuilder<? extends StreamChannel<List<? extends OUT>,List<? extends OUT>>> join(@NotNull
                                                                                                                    Iterable<? extends Channel.OutputChannel<? extends OUT>> channels)
        Returns a builder of stream channels joining the data coming from the specified ones.
        An output will be generated only when at least one result is available for each channel.
